ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for NIS/CIS
Source: ITAR/TASS News Agency, 10 Jul 2000 [edited

According to the Provincial Health Care Committee in Volgograd province, a
third death (a woman) caused by Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever [virus has
been registered in Kotelnikovsk region. At the present time about 30 people
are under physician's control in hospitals. In addition, more than 130
citizens, who had been bitten by the ticks, in the region, are under medical
observation.
